{"id":"10595","name":"[MacOS] Menubar Countdown Timer","tagline":"Timer shortcut for MacOS that uses Menubar Countdown","icon":"ios15 c946986751 g61512","latest":"30828","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Timer shortcut for MacOS. If you ask Siri to set a timer on MacOS, it'll create a reminder for the end time instead of setting a timer because MacOS doesn't have a built in timer app. This shortcut uses the free <a href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/menubar-countdown/id1485343244?mt=12\">Menubar Countdown</a> app.</p>\n<h2>Features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Utilizes AppleScript to set and start the timer on the Menubar Countdown app</li>\n<li>Once timer is set, a confirmation notification with the timer end time is displayed</li>\n<li>Calculates hours and minutes from a single prompt for minutes</li>\n<li>Displays the timer in your Mac menu bar (although my shortcut doesn't do this, the Menubar Countdown app does this)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Permissions</h2>\n<p>In the Shortcuts preferences &gt; Advanced &gt; Allow Running Scripts needs to be enabled. The first time you run the shortcut, you will be prompted to check this setting.</p>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - Nov. 29, 2021, 4:50 a.m.</strong></p>"}